WEBVTT

00:30.080 --> 00:32.197
(EXPLOSIONS)

00:41.280 --> 00:43.112
(EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE)

01:10.000 --> 01:11.056
OLIVER NORTH: <i>Last question.</i>

01:11.080 --> 01:15.438
<i>Fifty years from now, some youngster's
gonna pull this disc out of a box</i>

01:15.520 --> 01:18.672
<i>and maybe make a judgment
about becoming a journalist.</i>

01:20.080 --> 01:24.711
<i>What would you want that youngster
to know about Marie Colvin</i>

01:24.800 --> 01:27.872
<i>and about being
a war correspondent?</i>

01:29.680 --> 01:30.776
MARIE COLVIN:
<i>Very difficult question.</i>

01:30.800 --> 01:34.271
<i>It's like writing, uh,
your own obituary.</i>

01:35.160 --> 01:39.279
<i>I suppose to look back at it and say,
you know, I cared enough</i>

01:39.360 --> 01:44.230
<i>to go to these places
and write, in some way,</i>

01:44.320 --> 01:49.679
<i>something that would make someone
else care as much about it</i>

01:49.760 --> 01:51.672
<i>as I did at the time.</i>

01:51.760 --> 01:56.437
<i>Part of it is you're never
gonna get to where you're going</i>

01:56.520 --> 01:59.672
<i>if you acknowledge fear.</i>

01:59.760 --> 02:02.320
<i>I think fear comes later,</i>
(CHUCKLES) <i>when it's all over.</i>

02:15.600 --> 02:17.831
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:18.480 --> 02:20.312
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

02:23.840 --> 02:25.274
(LAUGHTER)

02:26.640 --> 02:28.711
(MARIE MOANING)

02:28.800 --> 02:30.678
(KEYS CLATTER)

02:37.600 --> 02:39.239
(LAPTOP BEEPS)

02:40.560 --> 02:42.836
(DAVID INHALES SHARPLY)

02:45.720 --> 02:47.359
- Are you stuck?
- Yeah.

02:48.840 --> 02:50.274
Struggling with the end.

02:51.160 --> 02:52.992
The hero always
gets the girl.

02:55.160 --> 02:57.072
It's a book
about naval warfare,

02:57.160 --> 02:59.117
but I will
keep that in mind.

02:59.240 --> 03:00.674
(CHUCKLES)

03:02.960 --> 03:04.280
(GROANS)

03:07.480 --> 03:09.233
(GRUNTING)

03:10.800 --> 03:12.314
(MARIE MOANS)

03:19.120 --> 03:20.634
We should get married again.

03:22.080 --> 03:23.799
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

03:23.880 --> 03:27.271
It didn't work so well
last time, did it?

03:28.800 --> 03:30.234
We can go sailing.

03:30.360 --> 03:33.512
I was looking at Antigua.
It's beautiful.

03:34.520 --> 03:35.749
(CHUCKLES)

03:36.640 --> 03:38.359
I wanna try for a baby again.

03:41.160 --> 03:42.799
I don't think
that's a good idea.

03:43.880 --> 03:44.950
Why not?

03:46.960 --> 03:48.155
We tried.

03:50.920 --> 03:53.037
You're not 35 anymore.

03:55.480 --> 03:57.199
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:01.480 --> 04:02.630
- Zoe?
- Yeah.

04:02.760 --> 04:04.399
- Is Simon in Palestine?
- No.

04:04.480 --> 04:06.756
Oh, for fuck's sake.
<i>The Telegraph</i> are already there.

04:06.840 --> 04:08.280
We're gonna lose the scoop
on Arafat.

04:09.360 --> 04:10.555
Who else could go?

04:10.680 --> 04:11.830
Oh, shit.

04:14.840 --> 04:16.069
Blue screen of death.

04:17.040 --> 04:18.040
(GRUNTS)

04:18.120 --> 04:19.315
Let me, um...

04:19.440 --> 04:21.671
You just control, alt
and then delete,

04:21.760 --> 04:24.798
and then you just hold it down for,
like, three or four seconds.

04:25.040 --> 04:26.040
(LAPTOP WHINES)

04:26.160 --> 04:27.276
There you go.

04:28.200 --> 04:30.351
- Thanks. Are you new?
- (CHUCKLES)

04:30.440 --> 04:32.671
Yeah, I am.
I'm Kate Richardson.

04:32.760 --> 04:34.479
Just started on
the foreign desk last week.

04:34.560 --> 04:37.234
- Oh, great. Marie Colvin.
- Yeah, I know who you are.

04:38.680 --> 04:42.435
I'm your biggest fan.
I'd love to pick your brain sometime.

04:42.520 --> 04:43.556
Well...

04:44.920 --> 04:46.752
My first word of advice

04:49.360 --> 04:52.273
is don't do anything
he tries to get you to do.

04:52.360 --> 04:53.589
Who?

04:53.720 --> 04:57.475
Hey, Marie. I need you
in Palestine, not Sri Lanka.

04:57.600 --> 05:00.195
Sean, there is
an unreported war there.

05:00.360 --> 05:02.656
Yes, because journalists have been
banned for more than six years.

05:02.680 --> 05:03.796
I can't let you go.

05:03.920 --> 05:05.718
Thousands
of starving children.

05:05.800 --> 05:07.792
If the government catches you,
they'll kill you.

05:07.880 --> 05:08.916
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

05:09.000 --> 05:11.799
Look, I have an interview
with a Tamil rebel leader.

05:11.880 --> 05:13.394
Find someone else.

05:14.320 --> 05:15.436
Sri Lanka.

05:18.320 --> 05:20.198
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

05:33.240 --> 05:34.674
(DISTANT GUNFIRE)

05:36.560 --> 05:38.153
(LOUD GUNFIRE)

05:57.360 --> 06:01.274
THAMILSELVAN: The government refuses
to let UN aid through their siege lines.

06:01.360 --> 06:04.194
Well, the government's denying
there's an embargo on the Vanni.

06:04.880 --> 06:06.200
The government lies.

06:06.280 --> 06:07.873
(MAN SHOUTS IN SINHALESE)

06:08.480 --> 06:12.474
You have a reputation for speaking honestly,
Miss Colvin.

06:13.640 --> 06:15.376
- People listen to you.
- (INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

06:15.400 --> 06:16.914
You must let the world know

06:17.000 --> 06:20.471
the Tamil Tigers are willing
for a political settlement.

06:21.280 --> 06:22.919
We only demand equal rights.

06:23.040 --> 06:25.635
Look, that all goes back
to British colonial rule.

06:26.320 --> 06:29.040
I can't fix that. Anyway,
that's not why I'm here.

06:29.760 --> 06:32.673
Then what will
you write about?

06:35.200 --> 06:37.635
Half of the people
living here are starving,

06:37.720 --> 06:39.120
and the other half are sick.

06:39.960 --> 06:41.599
Sure, the government
is blockading aid,

06:41.680 --> 06:45.390
but what little gets through is
stolen by your own Tiger army.

06:45.480 --> 06:48.518
There are people dying here and
nobody knows it's happening.

06:53.840 --> 06:55.593
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

07:00.360 --> 07:01.999
(FLIES BUZZING)

07:20.240 --> 07:22.835
MARIE: <i>In war zones,
parents go to bed at night</i>

07:22.960 --> 07:25.429
<i>not knowing if their children
will see the morning.</i>

07:26.880 --> 07:30.430
<i>That is a measure of fear
that I can never feel.</i>

07:33.640 --> 07:35.518
<i>But when
you're covering a war,</i>

07:35.640 --> 07:38.155
<i>you have to go to places
where you could be killed,</i>

07:38.240 --> 07:40.516
<i>or where others
are being killed...</i>

07:40.600 --> 07:42.876
(LEADER SHOUTS IN SINHALESE)

07:42.960 --> 07:43.960
(IN ENGLISH) Go there.

07:45.880 --> 07:50.830
MARIE: <i>...and put one foot in front of
the other, no matter how afraid you are,</i>

07:50.920 --> 07:53.515
<i>to make that suffering
part of the record.</i>

08:08.120 --> 08:10.316
Is it safe?
Is it safe to walk through?

08:10.440 --> 08:12.830
Only this way out.
Only this side.

08:12.920 --> 08:14.752
- Is this the only way out?
- This way.

08:14.840 --> 08:15.840
Okay.

08:22.680 --> 08:25.320
(MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

08:26.920 --> 08:28.798
- (GUNS FIRING)
- (MARIE GASPING)

08:34.120 --> 08:35.918
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

08:38.360 --> 08:39.679
LEADER: Marie, be careful.

08:39.760 --> 08:41.114
(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)

08:44.159 --> 08:45.310
Stay down.

08:45.400 --> 08:46.754
I'm not armed!

08:47.480 --> 08:48.994
Journalist! American!

08:49.080 --> 08:50.434
(EXPLOSION)

08:52.680 --> 08:54.990
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

08:58.320 --> 08:59.674
(GROANS)

08:59.760 --> 09:01.319
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

09:06.240 --> 09:08.152
Get your hands off me.
I can't see.

09:08.920 --> 09:10.877
Where am I?
I can't see.

09:12.040 --> 09:14.256
Get your hands off me. I can't see.
MEDIC: Calm down. It's okay.

09:14.280 --> 09:17.000
Where am I?
Oh, my God. I can't see.

09:23.760 --> 09:25.319
(RETCHES)

09:26.560 --> 09:28.950
(DOCTOR SPEAKING SINHALESE)

09:42.440 --> 09:45.160
- (IN ENGLISH) You must rest, Miss Colvin.
- I need my notebook.

09:51.960 --> 09:53.030
Conc...

09:54.720 --> 09:59.431
Conciliatory words do not
come easy to Thamilselvan,

09:59.520 --> 10:02.194
the second in command
of the Tamil Tigers.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.760
The walking stick he carries

10:09.840 --> 10:14.710
is a legacy of the three times
he was shot in battle

10:14.880 --> 10:18.840
since the beginning of the
bloody war for independence.

10:22.240 --> 10:24.277
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

10:33.120 --> 10:34.474
(EXPLOSION)

10:38.040 --> 10:39.440
(EXPLOSIONS)

10:44.680 --> 10:45.796
(PANTING)

10:54.360 --> 10:56.477
(DOORBELL RINGING)

10:58.960 --> 11:00.917
David. Door.

11:01.000 --> 11:02.150
DAVID: I've got it.

11:08.400 --> 11:10.596
- (GUNFIRE)
- (MARIE PANTING)

11:12.440 --> 11:15.433
He's looking at me with
such tenderness and concern

11:15.520 --> 11:19.036
and I just can't stand it
anymore, and he says,

11:19.120 --> 11:21.271
"We can try
to save the eye."

11:21.360 --> 11:25.718
And I said, "Not until you turn
off that fucking whale music."

11:25.800 --> 11:27.519
(ALL LAUGHING)

11:30.960 --> 11:32.256
- Whoa, whoa!
- Hey, babe, let me.

11:32.280 --> 11:34.511
No, don't help me.
Don't you dare fucking help me.

11:34.600 --> 11:37.274
DAVID: All right, this is our last bottle.
Get it right.

11:37.360 --> 11:39.955
The table has had
more wine than I have.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.270
(MARIE CHUCKLES)

11:42.720 --> 11:44.200
DAVID: Go on. Go on.

11:44.400 --> 11:46.119
Oh.
DAVID: Oh.

11:46.200 --> 11:48.271
(RITA CHEERING AND CHUCKLING)

11:49.000 --> 11:50.000
RITA: Oh, here's one.

11:50.080 --> 11:54.074
"We Tamils are so proud of your brave
foreign correspondent, Marie Colvin.

11:54.160 --> 11:56.550
- Aw.
- "We appreciate her visit to the Vanni area

11:56.640 --> 11:58.200
"to bring the news
to the outside world,

11:58.320 --> 11:59.879
"and we wish her,
'Get well soon.'"

12:00.000 --> 12:02.879
Wow.
AMY: Sting and Trudie wish you well, too,

12:02.960 --> 12:07.000
and they said there are lots of famous
people who are blind in one eye.

12:07.120 --> 12:08.236
Um, Sammy Davis Jr.

12:08.320 --> 12:09.720
The bloke from Radiohead.

12:10.520 --> 12:12.280
- (SNAPS FINGERS) James Joyce.
- Moshe Dayan.

12:12.360 --> 12:14.272
- DAVID: Moshe Dayan.
- (ALL LAUGHING)

12:14.360 --> 12:15.999
Oh! They all
wore eye patches.

12:16.080 --> 12:17.958
Eye patch.
What an amazing idea.

12:18.040 --> 12:20.077
That is the worst idea
I've ever heard.

12:20.160 --> 12:22.231
- Babe.
- I'm not a fucking pirate.

12:22.320 --> 12:23.436
AMY: You'd look great.

12:23.520 --> 12:26.513
You would look so sexy.

12:27.360 --> 12:29.795
- For me, my darling.
- This is absolutely happening.

12:29.880 --> 12:31.030
(DAVID LAUGHING)

12:49.880 --> 12:51.678
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

12:57.000 --> 12:58.593
(CRIES SOFTLY)

13:09.840 --> 13:11.593
(SOBBING)

13:14.320 --> 13:15.515
(ALL CHEERING)

13:15.600 --> 13:16.750
DAVID: Here's Amy.

13:17.560 --> 13:22.032
AMY: You look great, Marie.
You look amazing.

13:23.200 --> 13:25.795
- So good to see you.
- You, too. You, too.

13:26.440 --> 13:28.352
Congratulations.

13:28.440 --> 13:31.399
On behalf of the newspaper,
a very large thank you.

13:31.480 --> 13:34.359
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

13:34.440 --> 13:36.272
- Hey.
- Hi.

13:36.360 --> 13:39.239
- Can I get you another drink?
- No. Let me.

13:40.320 --> 13:43.392
I will leave you two
to talk shop.

13:43.520 --> 13:45.193
Thank you.

13:45.280 --> 13:47.795
- Don't stand there. I can't see you.
- Oh, sorry.

13:48.320 --> 13:49.754
- Is that better?
- Yeah.

13:53.720 --> 13:56.554
- Was that the best you had?
- Yeah.

13:59.640 --> 14:02.678
- People are calling it stupid.
- The picture?

14:02.800 --> 14:04.280
No, you going in.

14:05.040 --> 14:06.872
Well, I think stupid
is writing a column

14:07.000 --> 14:08.832
about the dinner party
you went to last night.

14:10.680 --> 14:11.955
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

14:12.680 --> 14:15.120
The paper will do anything you want.
You know that, don't you?

14:16.640 --> 14:17.756
Anything?

14:18.760 --> 14:22.720
Yeah,
you were our best asset on the foreign desk.

14:23.720 --> 14:24.790
Were?

14:28.720 --> 14:31.110
I'm not hanging up
my flak jacket, Sean.

14:32.000 --> 14:35.516
Good.
Glad we got that cleared up.

14:38.560 --> 14:40.677
(DAVID AND WOMAN LAUGHING)

14:43.680 --> 14:45.592
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

14:47.880 --> 14:49.599
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

14:49.680 --> 14:53.151
SEAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
our Foreign Correspondent of the Year,

14:53.240 --> 14:57.632
known for racking up the largest sat
phone bill in <i>Sunday Times</i> history,

14:57.720 --> 15:00.394
our very own living legend,

15:02.160 --> 15:03.435
Marie Colvin.

15:03.520 --> 15:05.318
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

15:33.520 --> 15:34.749
Do you ever have nightmares?

15:36.400 --> 15:37.550
- What?
- Nightmares.

15:37.640 --> 15:38.915
From when you were
in the field.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.195
Yeah.

15:44.200 --> 15:45.270
Bosnia.

15:47.120 --> 15:50.909
Serb soldiers posing
with decapitated heads.

15:51.760 --> 15:53.717
They seemed very pleased
with themselves.

15:55.320 --> 15:57.073
Still have it sometimes.

15:58.400 --> 16:00.073
When were you
gonna call her?

16:03.440 --> 16:04.556
Who?

16:05.520 --> 16:06.520
The girl.

16:08.800 --> 16:10.359
I'm guessing
you got her number.

16:12.040 --> 16:13.599
Thank you. Keep it.

16:13.680 --> 16:16.320
Yeah, yeah, okay,
I got her number.

16:17.080 --> 16:19.231
I was gonna
call her tomorrow.

16:20.120 --> 16:22.635
Or maybe the day after.
Or maybe I wasn't. I don't know.

16:23.200 --> 16:24.256
That's the level of respect
you have for me.

16:24.280 --> 16:27.830
Oh, come on, you are constantly
leaving me for some faraway place.

16:27.920 --> 16:30.799
Despite that,
I've always been here for you.

16:30.920 --> 16:34.118
- I never asked you to be.
- You shouldn't have gone to Sri Lanka.

16:35.200 --> 16:37.635
I told you to stop
all this so long ago,

16:37.720 --> 16:40.110
and you are like
a moth to a bloody flame.

16:40.960 --> 16:42.155
I mean, look at you.

16:42.880 --> 16:45.031
You were so beautiful.

16:46.320 --> 16:47.800
Well, fuck off.

16:47.880 --> 16:50.952
Go on. Fuck off,
back to your novels.

16:54.680 --> 16:57.434
(EXPLOSION SOUNDS)

16:57.520 --> 16:59.591
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

17:07.599 --> 17:08.636
(GRUNTS)

17:10.280 --> 17:12.317
(EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE)

17:12.599 --> 17:13.750
(PANTING)

17:16.119 --> 17:17.759
(GUNS FIRING)

17:19.200 --> 17:21.237
(TRUCK RATTLING)

17:30.120 --> 17:31.998
(HORN BLARING)

17:41.120 --> 17:42.679
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

17:43.320 --> 17:45.118
(TRUCK STOPS)

17:45.200 --> 17:46.759
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

17:46.840 --> 17:49.071
(DOOR OPENS)

17:49.160 --> 17:51.117
(MEN SPEAKING KURDISH)

17:59.520 --> 18:02.797
(IN ENGLISH) Hey, get your hands off me.
Hands off.

18:11.000 --> 18:12.559
(GROANS)

18:31.080 --> 18:32.116
MOURAD: Miss Mary.

18:33.160 --> 18:34.480
Mourad.

18:35.320 --> 18:36.674
Oh.

18:39.480 --> 18:41.949
- You came in the potato truck!
- I came in the potato truck.

18:43.240 --> 18:45.880
- (CHUCKLES) Nice. Nice eye patch.
- Oh, thank you, Mourad.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.000
And how are you?

18:47.120 --> 18:49.680
Ah, I made it to lunchtime
in one piece, so I'm thankful.

18:51.200 --> 18:52.714
Shit. You know,
we're gonna be late.

18:52.800 --> 18:56.350
I wanna pick something up in the
Green Zone before we go to Fallujah.

18:56.440 --> 18:57.476
Okay <i>. Yalla. Yalla.</i>

18:57.920 --> 18:59.991
(REBELS CHANTING IN KURDISH)

19:03.160 --> 19:05.231
MOURAD: (IN ENGLISH)
So good to see you, Miss Mary.

19:05.320 --> 19:06.879
MARIE: (CHUCKLES)
Am I glad to see you.

19:14.000 --> 19:15.000
(STARTS ENGINE)

19:30.240 --> 19:31.469
OFFICER: While here,

19:31.560 --> 19:35.520
you are considered guests of the
Coalition Provisional Authority.

19:36.480 --> 19:41.077
Refusal to cooperate with
the rules as we've outlined

19:41.200 --> 19:42.350
for embedded reporters

19:42.440 --> 19:46.150
will result in an immediate
revocation of press privileges.

19:46.640 --> 19:51.192
You must remain with that unit for the
entire duration of the assignment.

19:51.280 --> 19:52.919
God, we used to go
wherever we wanted.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.150
Hey, Norm.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.071
It's like they're drugging
the fucking journalists.

19:57.160 --> 19:59.038
- Yeah.
- You will be disembedded.

19:59.560 --> 20:03.270
- How you holding up?
- I still can't measure distances.

20:04.040 --> 20:06.396
Who knew your left eye
was so important?

20:06.480 --> 20:07.709
(CHUCKLES)

20:07.840 --> 20:10.912
- When was the last time you slept?
- Ah, I don't sleep.

20:12.000 --> 20:13.229
Where you headed?

20:13.320 --> 20:14.913
God, you gotta be
more subtle than that.

20:15.000 --> 20:17.720
Oh, come on. After everything
I did for you in East Timor?

20:17.840 --> 20:19.656
- What have you got?
- East Timor? Sure, I remember you.

20:19.680 --> 20:21.876
Riding off into the sunset
with the UN.

20:21.960 --> 20:23.599
At least
I saved you a seat.

20:23.680 --> 20:25.239
- You were in East Timor?
- Yeah.

20:25.320 --> 20:27.039
Back when you were
still in college.

20:27.160 --> 20:29.197
Ah. Never went to college.

20:29.280 --> 20:32.159
Oh, God. I'm fucking
done after this.

20:32.240 --> 20:34.516
Oh, Norm, you wouldn't
know what else to do.

20:34.600 --> 20:37.354
And you couldn't live
with the fear of missing out.

20:37.480 --> 20:41.269
All right,
let's have television media head this way,

20:41.360 --> 20:43.875
print media,
back of the hangar.

20:44.400 --> 20:46.278
Well, welcome back.
Hey, we missed you.

20:46.360 --> 20:47.874
See you at the Hamra, Norm.

20:47.960 --> 20:50.077
- Save me a seat at the bar.
- You bet.

20:52.920 --> 20:54.115
KATE: I'm not getting angry.

20:54.200 --> 20:55.520
You're not letting me
do my job.

20:57.800 --> 20:59.029
What's your name?

20:59.960 --> 21:01.519
- Paul.
- I'm Marie.

21:01.920 --> 21:04.355
- I know.
- So, you're freelance?

21:04.440 --> 21:05.954
- Always.
- Any good?

21:07.160 --> 21:08.276
The best.

21:10.840 --> 21:12.320
- Come on.
- What, now?

21:13.240 --> 21:14.754
I need a photographer.

21:14.840 --> 21:16.957
I've never found one I like.
Let's see how you do.

21:17.040 --> 21:18.793
- Now? (CHUCKLES)
- Yeah.

21:18.920 --> 21:21.913
You don't think I subscribe
to all that bullshit, do you?

21:23.120 --> 21:25.077
- Where are we going?
- Fallujah.

21:25.160 --> 21:26.276
(CHUCKLES)

21:26.400 --> 21:29.950
- We can't just drive to Fallujah.
- Why not?

21:30.840 --> 21:32.991
- 'Cause we'll be targeted.
- Are you scared?

21:34.640 --> 21:37.314
- No.
- Good.

21:42.880 --> 21:44.712
MARIE: Feras says
he personally drove

21:44.800 --> 21:47.918
a truck full of bodies to a desert
camp overlooking Lake Habbaniyah.

21:48.040 --> 21:49.256
SEAN: <i>Now, listen to me.
Listen, Marie...</i>

21:49.280 --> 21:52.432
Six hundred people killed
by Saddam in 1991,

21:52.520 --> 21:55.672
buried in trenches
60 miles west of Baghdad.

21:56.480 --> 21:59.678
We won't get to it if we're behind
the American advance.

22:00.040 --> 22:02.111
<i>- It's not an option.</i>
- Well, no.

22:02.200 --> 22:04.795
- We're going to Fallujah.
- It's too dangerous.

22:04.880 --> 22:06.314
Everywhere's too dangerous.

22:06.400 --> 22:09.711
What about the Ramadi story,
Saddam's men working with Al-Qaeda?

22:09.800 --> 22:13.555
There's no source on that yet,
but trust me on the mass grave.

22:14.120 --> 22:16.271
People have been searching
for this for years.

22:16.360 --> 22:18.352
Okay, well, then,
I need you to find bodies.

22:18.480 --> 22:19.880
I'll call you when I do.

22:20.960 --> 22:21.996
Fuck.

22:25.480 --> 22:27.119
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

22:33.120 --> 22:34.270
MOURAD: Miss Mary.

22:35.800 --> 22:37.029
They're not American.

22:37.120 --> 22:39.840
They're either Saddam's police
or his militia.

22:39.960 --> 22:41.758
They're not gonna want us here
either way.

22:47.360 --> 22:49.272
(MOURAD CLEARS THROAT)

22:56.240 --> 22:57.640
(CORPORAL SPEAKS ARABIC)

22:57.720 --> 22:59.680
MOURAD: (IN ENGLISH)
He wants to know who you are.

23:00.120 --> 23:01.634
(SPEAKS ARABIC)

23:03.840 --> 23:05.672
(IN ENGLISH)
Sir, we're aid workers.

23:05.760 --> 23:08.594
We're here to help the doctors
in Lake Habbaniyah.

23:08.680 --> 23:11.479
(MOURAD SPEAKING ARABIC)

23:17.200 --> 23:19.999
(IN ENGLISH) See? I'm a nurse.
This says "health."

23:20.080 --> 23:21.080
"Health."

23:21.160 --> 23:22.640
(MOURAD SPEAKING ARABIC)

23:30.400 --> 23:31.800
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

23:40.960 --> 23:42.030
PAUL: Fuck me.

23:43.440 --> 23:44.715
Was that your gym card?

23:48.400 --> 23:51.199
All right. Here we go.

23:51.280 --> 23:54.239
(SOLDIERS SHOUT IN ARABIC)

23:54.320 --> 23:55.680
PAUL: Yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:56.440 --> 23:59.080
(SOLDIERS SPEAKING ARABIC)

24:01.000 --> 24:03.117
(THUDDING)

24:11.960 --> 24:13.997
(SHOUTS IN ARABIC)

24:23.120 --> 24:25.296
(IN ENGLISH) He wants to know
where your medical equipment is.

24:25.320 --> 24:26.800
Tell him it's gone ahead.

24:26.880 --> 24:28.872
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

24:40.360 --> 24:42.511
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

24:44.280 --> 24:46.920
(SOLDIERS WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY)

24:54.520 --> 24:56.079
(CAPTAIN SPEAKING ARABIC)

24:57.080 --> 24:58.594
(IN ENGLISH)
Turn around. Turn around.

25:05.200 --> 25:06.919
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

25:14.240 --> 25:15.435
(IN ENGLISH)
What's he saying?

25:17.360 --> 25:19.591
He said we don't need doctors
where we're going.

25:28.800 --> 25:30.314
CAPTAIN: <i>Yalla.</i>

25:33.880 --> 25:34.996
MARIE: Shall we go?

25:40.720 --> 25:41.790
Fuck.

25:41.920 --> 25:43.673
(ENGINE STARTS)

25:43.760 --> 25:44.989
Jesus Christ.

25:59.640 --> 26:00.756
Your fucking gym card.

26:00.840 --> 26:02.354
You burned me
with your cigarette.

26:02.440 --> 26:04.113
- (LAUGHS)
- I'm sorry. Fuck me.

26:04.200 --> 26:06.431
(BOTH WHOOPING)

26:09.880 --> 26:11.030
(SPEAKS ARABIC)

26:11.120 --> 26:12.270
MARIE: What's he saying?

26:12.360 --> 26:14.272
MOURAD: He's just apologizing
for being late.

26:14.360 --> 26:17.910
No problem. No problem.
(STUTTERING) Thank you for coming.

26:18.000 --> 26:21.437
I wanna start over there.
Is that okay?

26:21.520 --> 26:23.398
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

26:36.040 --> 26:37.997
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

26:42.440 --> 26:44.272
(MAN SPEAKING ARABIC)

27:00.600 --> 27:02.478
(METAL CREAKING)

27:14.840 --> 27:16.479
What if you don't
find anything?

27:26.960 --> 27:29.270
(WOMAN SPEAKING ARABIC)

27:40.960 --> 27:43.953
And I want to know the
stories of individual people.

27:44.040 --> 27:47.033
I want to tell their stories.
Can she tell me about her father?

27:47.120 --> 27:49.191
(MEN SHOUTING IN ARABIC)

28:03.520 --> 28:05.160
PAUL: (IN ENGLISH)
Don't fucking touch me.

28:05.680 --> 28:07.416
Paul, he wants the camera
and wants you to stop.

28:07.440 --> 28:08.440
No.

28:08.520 --> 28:10.096
There are hundreds of people
buried here.

28:10.120 --> 28:12.560
MOURAD: Miss Mary,
they're going to arrest us if we don't stop.

28:13.080 --> 28:14.673
Ask him whose side he's on.

28:15.640 --> 28:18.030
(SHOUTING IN ARABIC)

28:18.120 --> 28:19.920
(IN ENGLISH) Tell me in Arabic.
I'll tell him.

28:20.000 --> 28:21.920
- (INDISTINCT SHOUTING)
- (MARIE SPEAKING ARABIC)

28:24.320 --> 28:26.437
- (ALL CLAMORING)
- (WOMEN WAILING)

28:30.320 --> 28:33.074
Have some respect.
Have some respect.

28:33.920 --> 28:36.037
(WOMEN WAILING)

28:47.480 --> 28:49.358
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

28:52.120 --> 28:54.112
(MEN SPEAKING ARABIC)

28:57.920 --> 28:59.991
(CONTINUES WAILING)

29:07.760 --> 29:10.480
MEN: (CHANTING) <i>Allahu akbar.</i>

29:43.000 --> 29:46.072
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

29:53.880 --> 29:56.475
(WOMEN SINGING FUNERAL SONG)

29:59.960 --> 30:02.395
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

30:09.920 --> 30:11.195
(MARIE SNIFFLES)

30:17.640 --> 30:18.960
(SNIFFLES)

30:21.720 --> 30:23.518
(SINGING CONTINUES)

30:38.040 --> 30:40.874
REPORTER: (ON TV) <i>...allied forces
targeted key locations in Baghdad,</i>

30:40.960 --> 30:42.599
<i>the northern Mosul area</i>

30:42.680 --> 30:45.798
<i>as well as southern Iraq,
near the Iraq-Kuwait border.</i>

30:46.120 --> 30:48.919
<i>US officials have told us
that Saddam Hussein</i>

30:49.000 --> 30:52.152
<i>and some of his highest-ranking
officials are among the targets...</i>

31:00.400 --> 31:01.400
(SIGHS)

31:01.480 --> 31:04.359
- Paul, are you okay?
- I can't stop thinking about it.

31:09.440 --> 31:10.760
MARIE: Get another drink.

31:14.080 --> 31:16.231
- You want one?
- Not when I'm working.

31:17.920 --> 31:19.559
Are we selling
a phony war?

31:23.040 --> 31:25.680
Paul, what we saw,
was it phony?

31:27.640 --> 31:28.640
No.

31:30.200 --> 31:32.271
"War is not so terrible
for governments.

31:33.240 --> 31:37.200
"For they are not wounded or
killed like ordinary people."

31:39.400 --> 31:41.736
CORRESPONDENT: (ON TV) <i>While on patrol
today with the Seventh Brigade,</i>

31:41.760 --> 31:45.720
<i>we encountered fierce enemy fire from
insurgents on the outskirts of Baghdad.</i>

31:46.120 --> 31:48.635
<i>Meanwhile, it seems as though
we hit very strategic...</i>

31:48.760 --> 31:51.195
But she's calling
US forces "we."

31:52.120 --> 31:53.759
- Don't worry about it.
- Why not?

31:53.880 --> 31:55.314
Because it doesn't matter.

31:55.440 --> 31:58.433
It doesn't matter what type of
plane just bombed a village.

31:58.600 --> 32:02.276
What is important
is the human cost of the act.

32:02.440 --> 32:05.194
People connect with people,

32:05.280 --> 32:08.114
so you find their stories,
tell their stories,

32:08.200 --> 32:09.634
forget about the other stuff.

32:10.720 --> 32:12.074
You mean close your eyes?

32:12.200 --> 32:14.136
- She's already got one eye closed.
- It's not funny.

32:14.160 --> 32:15.674
Thanks.

32:15.800 --> 32:18.520
Look, this is
the rough draft of history.

32:19.920 --> 32:22.116
You have to find
the truth of it.

32:22.200 --> 32:24.317
If you lose that,
you're not helping anybody here.

32:24.400 --> 32:28.189
You're just making
yourself feel better.

32:36.280 --> 32:37.430
(SNIFFS)

32:37.520 --> 32:39.034
I'm going to bed.

32:39.120 --> 32:40.349
Right. Night, Kate.

32:42.640 --> 32:43.790
Sleep tight.

32:44.680 --> 32:45.830
Fuck off.

32:46.200 --> 32:47.236
(CHUCKLES)

32:50.560 --> 32:51.630
Oh, fuck.

32:52.520 --> 32:54.989
Paul, do you know
how to recover a file?

32:56.400 --> 32:57.400
(SIGHS)

32:57.480 --> 32:58.755
Give it over.

33:01.280 --> 33:02.430
(SNORTS)

33:05.800 --> 33:07.314
I don't know why I bother.

33:11.320 --> 33:13.312
I should just go back
to dictation.

33:17.520 --> 33:19.989
- (CHUCKLING) This is weird.
- What?

33:20.600 --> 33:25.550
I've always looked up to you,
and now here I am,

33:25.640 --> 33:27.871
saving your work
from your own folly.

33:32.160 --> 33:33.674
Have you saved my work?

33:33.760 --> 33:34.796
Wait.

33:36.280 --> 33:37.873
I'm not good under pressure.

33:40.080 --> 33:42.037
- (PAUL SIGHS)
- (CLICKING)

33:44.040 --> 33:46.316
- Ta-da.
- You're a bloody genius.

33:55.520 --> 33:56.670
(TYPING)

33:57.400 --> 33:58.800
(EXHALES)

34:00.680 --> 34:01.680
Night, Marie.

34:04.200 --> 34:05.200
Night.

34:25.719 --> 34:27.120
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

34:43.440 --> 34:48.674
MARIE: <i>Bones and decomposed robes emerged
amid the dirt of the machine's jaws.</i>

34:51.679 --> 34:53.478
<i>A small pelvis
that was unearthed</i>

34:53.560 --> 34:57.110
<i>appeared to have been that
of a young teenager.</i>

35:00.880 --> 35:02.633
(MARIE MOANS)

35:11.880 --> 35:16.193
<i>Limbs severed,
dirt and rock and flesh torn alike.</i>

35:24.280 --> 35:25.680
(GASPS SOFTLY)

35:32.400 --> 35:36.713
<i>The knowledge of the fragility of
the human body never leaves you</i>

35:36.800 --> 35:38.029
<i>once you've seen...</i>

35:44.120 --> 35:45.315
<i>Once you've seen</i>

35:47.480 --> 35:51.679
<i>how easily flesh can be rent
by hot bits of metal.</i>

35:58.880 --> 36:00.951
(MARIE BREATHING HEAVILY)

36:04.680 --> 36:06.000
<i>Once you've seen...</i>

36:07.960 --> 36:09.599
(MARIE BREATHING HEAVILY)

36:14.320 --> 36:16.198
(GASPING)

36:16.280 --> 36:17.953
(GROANING)

36:18.680 --> 36:19.680
(PANTING)

36:19.760 --> 36:20.910
Fuck.

36:26.160 --> 36:27.674
(CLATTERING)

36:36.480 --> 36:38.358
(EXHALING)

36:38.440 --> 36:40.397
(PHONE RINGING)

36:44.160 --> 36:45.389
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

36:45.480 --> 36:47.597
<i>Hey. It's Marie.
Leave a message if you want.</i>

36:47.680 --> 36:49.194
<i>Although I never
actually check this.</i>

36:49.280 --> 36:50.280
(SIGHS)

36:52.960 --> 36:54.952
It's just as well,
to be honest.

36:56.080 --> 36:57.594
I'm up to my neck
in politics

36:57.680 --> 36:59.672
and we need to report
on the recovery of the euro.

36:59.760 --> 37:01.911
Forget it.
Go with the mass grave.

37:02.000 --> 37:04.720
Have you actually spoken to her
since she got back from Baghdad?

37:04.800 --> 37:05.800
Of course I have.

37:09.440 --> 37:13.354
It's pretty grim
for a Sunday front page.

37:14.080 --> 37:16.959
Yeah. Is it provocative? Yes.

37:17.040 --> 37:18.997
Will it make people
choke on their cornflakes

37:19.080 --> 37:21.436
when they're reading
about these poor sods? Yes.

37:21.520 --> 37:24.718
We're onto a bloody winner.
Fuck the bloody euro.

37:27.200 --> 37:28.475
(CHUCKLES)

37:29.720 --> 37:33.111
Listen, I don't think I can come
and see you all this weekend.

37:33.200 --> 37:34.656
RITA: (ON PHONE) <i>Oh,
I really want you to see Chloe.</i>

37:34.680 --> 37:36.273
She's almost started walking.

37:37.160 --> 37:40.198
(SNIFFLES) And I just
saw that girl again.

37:40.760 --> 37:41.910
Who?

37:42.320 --> 37:43.993
(SOBS)

37:44.080 --> 37:48.279
That child's lifeless body.
I can't get it out of my head.

37:48.400 --> 37:52.599
- (CRYING) <i>I can't get her out of my head, Rita.</i>
- Which child, Marie? Marie?

37:52.680 --> 37:55.115
The girl
who's always on my bed.

37:55.200 --> 37:56.919
(PHONE CLATTERS)

37:59.080 --> 38:00.275
(SNIFFLES)

38:00.360 --> 38:02.397
(CRYING)

38:04.000 --> 38:05.480
(PHONE RINGING)

38:06.760 --> 38:08.035
(MARIE SNIFFLES)

38:08.120 --> 38:09.679
(CONTINUES RINGING)

38:09.760 --> 38:12.639
Oh, go on, fuck off.
Go on, fuck off.

38:12.720 --> 38:13.720
God. Okay.

38:13.800 --> 38:16.520
Just tell Sean
to stop fucking calling me.

38:16.600 --> 38:18.956
- I wanna be alone.
- Right, okay.

38:19.040 --> 38:20.076
Done.

38:21.120 --> 38:23.237
(SIGHS) Marie,
can we talk now, please?

38:23.360 --> 38:24.919
If you hold the sheet steady.

38:25.000 --> 38:28.072
You have been avoiding
this conversation for months.

38:29.960 --> 38:31.792
Do you think
you might have, you know,

38:32.720 --> 38:34.393
post-traumatic
stress disorder?

38:35.240 --> 38:36.276
No.

38:39.600 --> 38:41.398
PTSD is what soldiers get.

38:41.520 --> 38:44.136
Come on, we both know you can get it
from just witnessing a car accident.

38:44.160 --> 38:46.231
I think you need
to talk to someone.

38:46.360 --> 38:49.558
- I'm not crazy, Rita.
- (CHUCKLES) I'm not saying you're crazy.

38:51.880 --> 38:53.656
Sean doesn't have the balls
to stand up to you,

38:53.680 --> 38:56.559
or he doesn't want to because
you're his prize pig, but...

38:57.280 --> 38:58.600
(RITA BREATHES DEEPLY)

38:58.680 --> 39:00.239
You're not well.

39:01.240 --> 39:02.959
We just want you
to get help.

39:07.000 --> 39:08.593
(BELL TOLLING)

39:13.000 --> 39:14.680
PAUL: Thanks for letting me
come and visit.

39:23.480 --> 39:26.279
If you're not fucking crazy when
you come into a place like this,

39:26.360 --> 39:27.840
you definitely will be
if you get out.

39:32.080 --> 39:33.355
So is this
where you grew up?

39:35.240 --> 39:36.356
Huh.

39:36.440 --> 39:39.000
Yeah, that's the north shore
of Long Island.

39:39.080 --> 39:40.230
Oyster Bay.

39:41.880 --> 39:43.109
Not the ritzy part.

39:44.720 --> 39:47.076
Who's this? Your boyfriend?

39:48.320 --> 39:50.232
No, that's creepy.
That's my dad.

39:52.080 --> 39:53.150
Oh.

39:53.680 --> 39:54.796
Sorry.

39:59.360 --> 40:04.958
Marie, when bad shit happens,
your brain goes into shock.

40:06.600 --> 40:10.640
It... It locks the trauma in the
same place you process emotions,

40:10.760 --> 40:13.798
which isn't where
memories are meant to live.

40:14.840 --> 40:18.311
That's why
it feels so present.

40:20.200 --> 40:22.590
Is that why
you left the army?

40:22.680 --> 40:24.592
No. I was court-martialed.

40:25.720 --> 40:28.155
Planted some hashish
in my locker to get out.

40:29.080 --> 40:31.595
(BOTH LAUGH)

40:34.480 --> 40:35.960
(PAUL SIGHS)

40:36.880 --> 40:38.917
How long did it take you
to get better?

40:42.880 --> 40:44.314
A long bloody time.

40:48.440 --> 40:50.477
Marie, you've seen more war
than most soldiers.

40:52.040 --> 40:54.032
You have to take it seriously.

40:57.040 --> 40:58.360
(SIGHS)

41:00.280 --> 41:01.680
You want psychobabble?

41:03.640 --> 41:05.199
Right, I'll give it to you.
I...

41:07.560 --> 41:09.199
I really looked up
to my father.

41:10.360 --> 41:11.714
I was tormented
when he died

41:11.800 --> 41:15.919
because he never understood the fact
that I might have opinions of my own.

41:16.800 --> 41:18.553
I love my mother,
but I struggle with her

41:18.640 --> 41:24.238
because I can never be the suburban
housewife in the safe fucking life.

41:25.240 --> 41:28.119
I diet fiercely because
I don't wanna get fat,

41:28.200 --> 41:31.238
but I also have seen so many
people in the world go hungry,

41:31.320 --> 41:33.915
so I... I like to eat.

41:35.760 --> 41:36.830
I, um...

41:38.920 --> 41:40.434
(VOICE CRACKING)

41:40.560 --> 41:44.156
I wanna be a mom, like my sister,
but I've had two miscarriages

41:44.240 --> 41:47.074
and I have to accept the fact
that I might never be that.

41:55.040 --> 41:56.759
I fear growing old.

42:00.160 --> 42:02.152
But then I also fear
dying young.

42:11.600 --> 42:14.320
I'm most happy with a
vodka martini in my hand,

42:14.400 --> 42:15.595
but I can't

42:18.160 --> 42:21.710
stand the fact that the chatter
in my head won't go quiet

42:23.160 --> 42:25.277
until there's a quart of vodka
inside me.

42:31.520 --> 42:32.954
(SNIFFLES)

42:33.720 --> 42:35.552
I hate being in a war zone.

42:39.760 --> 42:41.479
But I also feel compelled,

42:44.520 --> 42:47.240
compelled to see it
for myself.

42:49.720 --> 42:51.200
Because you're addicted to it.

42:57.880 --> 42:59.155
(SCOFFS)

43:08.120 --> 43:09.839
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

43:13.520 --> 43:15.477
(SOBS)

43:22.720 --> 43:24.359
(SNIFFLES)

43:29.880 --> 43:31.109
You're all right.

43:33.160 --> 43:34.160
(SNIFFLING)

43:34.240 --> 43:35.276
PAUL: Hey.

43:41.800 --> 43:42.800
Hey.

43:45.880 --> 43:47.075
You're all right.

43:48.320 --> 43:50.198
(SOBBING)

43:56.400 --> 43:58.517
(CHUCKLES) Sorry.

43:58.600 --> 43:59.920
It's all right.

44:02.360 --> 44:03.360
It's allowed.

44:03.440 --> 44:04.920
(LAUGHS)

44:06.400 --> 44:07.550
(SNIFFLES)

44:11.400 --> 44:13.790
(LAUGHING) Who did you say
my father looked like?

44:23.800 --> 44:25.075
Aww.

44:27.720 --> 44:29.154
(CHUCKLES)

44:37.920 --> 44:40.833
- What do you think?
- Suits you.

44:40.920 --> 44:44.197
Yeah, well, black seemed
so grim suddenly.

44:45.400 --> 44:47.631
Do you, um... Do you need
some more flowers?

44:49.680 --> 44:51.433
Thank you.
That's very sweet of you.

44:55.640 --> 44:57.757
Iraq, Afghanistan,
Blair, Bush.

44:57.880 --> 44:59.553
Now, we're struggling
to cover it all.

45:00.880 --> 45:03.349
- Thank you.
- Thank you for what?

45:04.240 --> 45:05.674
For trying to flatter me.

45:06.280 --> 45:09.041
I didn't come here to flatter you.
I came here to see how you're doing.

45:11.200 --> 45:12.520
And to, um...

45:15.480 --> 45:17.073
You can speak freely.

45:18.840 --> 45:21.196
Paul and I became
quite close in Iraq.

45:24.200 --> 45:25.554
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

45:27.680 --> 45:29.558
Can you give us a moment,
please, Paul?

45:32.920 --> 45:34.036
Sure.

45:46.520 --> 45:47.520
Are you okay?

45:51.680 --> 45:52.716
Mmm.

45:55.280 --> 45:56.680
We miss you, Marie.

45:57.920 --> 46:01.596
You have a God-given talent
to make people stop and care.

46:02.920 --> 46:04.434
(SCOFFS)

46:10.520 --> 46:13.035
Where do you see yourself
in 10 years, Sean?

46:13.120 --> 46:14.440
(CHUCKLES)

46:15.440 --> 46:16.999
Haven't really
thought about it.

46:17.080 --> 46:18.992
Don't be English.
Be honest.

46:20.680 --> 46:22.696
